<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-563-209  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 563 209.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  Oct 18 1990* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>New for Macintosh: Russian font translator from glps. (glpsProducts' Russian Central) (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>McMullen, Barbara E.; McMullen, John F.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   glps Products (Product introduction).andO;Product:   Russian Central (Computer program) (Product introduction)Text Oasis (Computer program) (Marketing).andO;Topic:     Software PublishersProduct IntroductionFontsRussian language.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>NEW FOR MACINTOSH: Russian Font Translator From glps CHAPEL HILL, NORTHCAROLINA, U.S.A., 1990 OCT 18 (NB) -- glps Products has announced RussianCentral, a program which allows the conversion of Russian text to and from alarge number of commercial and widely used public domain Russian fontformats.andP;  The product is available immediately at a cost of $49.95.andM;According to the announcement, the Russian font market is fragmented by 20commercial fonts, each using different computer codes, and Russian Central isable to move text between them.andP;  It also contains files which are used totransliterate Russian from the Cyrillic alphabet to the Latin alphabet andback.andM;Russian Central's processing requires the availability of glps' Text Oasisdesk accessory which sells separately for $49.95.andP;  Russian Central and TextOasis may be purchased as a bundle for $89.95.andP;  Text Oasis can create a listof words from mixed English and foreign-language text, sort a list of wordsor phrases alphabetically, count words, and change letter case.andM;Additionally, Text Oasis handles accent marks, capitalization andalphabetical order correctly.andP;  Its ability to convert text from one font orcharacter set to another, using predefined conversion tables, is the basis ofRussian Central's processing.andP;  The system will work with any Russian fontsand is not dependent on glps' Russian fonts.andM;glps Products is a Chapel Hill, NC, company owned by David Moffat who taughtcomputer science at NC State University for 10 years before leaving to devotefull time to foreign language studies and software.andP;  glps has previouslydeveloped other Macintosh software in Russian including the BilingualSolution system software, which integrates Russian into the standard EnglishMac; the Vocabulary Creator, for creating Russian- English andEnglish-Russian glossaries; LaserWriter and DeskWriter fonts for Russian; andan online Russian-English glossary.andM;(Barbara E. McMullen andamp; John F. McMullen/19901017/Press Contact: David Moffat,glps Products, 919-968-6780)</TEXT></DOC>